<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.1//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml11/DTD/xhtml11.dtd">
<html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
 <head>
  <title>CSS Test: Named pages: syntax</title>
  <link rel="author" title="Tom Clancy" href="mailto:tclancy@revenution.com"/>
  <link rel="help" href="http://www.w3.org/TR/css3-page/#using-named-pages"/>
  <meta name="flags" content="paged" />
  <meta name="assert" content="The syntax of the 'page' property is auto | identifier."/>
  <style type="text/css"><![CDATA[
  	@page {
		size: portrait;
		@top-center { content: "Auto"; }
	}
	@page rotated { 
		size: landscape; 
		@top-center { content: "Identifier"; }
	}
	div { page: rotated; }
  ]]></style>
 </head>
 <body>
 	<p>This page should be printed in portrait orientation (the short sides of the page are top and bottom). This page should say &quot;Auto&quot; in the top center.</p>
	<div>This page should be printed in landscape layout (the long sides of the page are top and bottom). This page should say &quot;Identifier&quot; in the top center.</div>
 </body>
</html>